# 🗄️ SQL (BigQuery)

This folder contains SQL projects completed during the **Turing College Data Analytics Program** using **Google BigQuery**. These projects demonstrate my ability to write efficient SQL queries, explore relational databases, and solve real-world business problems through data analysis.

## Projects

### 1. Relational Data Exploration (Intermediate SQL)

Focused on building a strong foundation in SQL by working with relational databases. The project covers:

- Filtering and sorting data
- Joins and relationships
- Aggregate functions
- GROUP BY and HAVING
- CASE statements
- Subqueries
- Common business reporting queries

### 2. Advanced Data Exploration (Advanced SQL)

Built upon the fundamentals by solving more complex analytical problems using advanced SQL techniques, including:

- Common Table Expressions (CTEs)
- Window Functions
- Complex Joins
- Nested Queries
- Date & Time Functions
- Advanced Aggregations
- Query Optimization
- Business KPI Analysis

## Tools

- Google BigQuery
- SQL (Standard SQL)

These projects strengthened my ability to transform raw relational data into meaningful business insights using SQL.
